description: Describes one or more network interface trunk associations.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: One or more filters. gre-key - The ID of a trunk interface association. interface-protocol - The interface protocol. Valid values are VLAN and GRE. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. If you specify multiple filters, the filters are joined with an AND, and the request returns only results that match all of the specified filters. For more information, see List and filter using the CLI and API in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. Name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. Values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. If you specify multiple values for a filter, the values are joined with an OR, and the request returns all results that match any of the specified values. (string) ---

nested_items.name: BranchInterfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of the branch network interface.

nested_items.name: TrunkInterfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of the trunk network interface.

nested_items.name: InterfaceProtocol
nested_items.description: The interface protocol. Valid values are VLAN and GRE.

nested_items.name: VlanId
nested_items.description: The ID of the VLAN when you use the VLAN protocol.

nested_items.name: GreKey
nested_items.description: The application key when you use the GRE protocol.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: The tags for the trunk interface association.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to use to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.
